    { question: 'What is a delta?', 'options': ['A landform at the mouth of a river', 'A type of cloud', 'A kind of storm', 'A layer of the atmosphere'], 'answer': 'A landform at the mouth of a river', explanation: 'A delta is a fan-shaped piece of land made of mud and sand that a river drops off just as it flows into a bigger body of water.' },
    { question: 'What is a geyser?', 'options': ['A hot spring that erupts steam and water', 'A type of volcano', 'A kind of earthquake', 'A layer of the Earth'], 'answer': 'A hot spring that erupts steam and water', explanation: 'A geyser is like a water volcano! It\'s a special hot spring that shoots a tall jet of hot water and steam up into the air!' },
    { question: 'What is a hot spring?', 'options': ['A spring of naturally hot water', 'A spring of cold water', 'A spring of salty water', 'A spring of muddy water'], 'answer': 'A spring of naturally hot water', explanation: 'A hot spring is where warm water from deep inside the Earth comes up to the surface. It\'s like a natural hot tub!' },
    { question: 'What are the polar ice caps?', 'options': ['Large sheets of ice at the North and South Poles', 'Large bodies of water at the North and South Poles', 'Large areas of land at the North and South Poles', 'Large mountains at the North and South Poles'], 'answer': 'Large sheets of ice at the North and South Poles', explanation: 'The polar ice caps are huge areas of thick ice and snow covering the top and bottom of our planet.' },
    { question: 'What is the difference between a sea and an ocean?', 'options': ['A sea is smaller than an ocean', 'A sea is saltier than an ocean', 'A sea is deeper than an ocean', 'There is no difference'], 'answer': 'A sea is smaller than an ocean', explanation: 'An ocean is a huge body of salt water, and a sea is a smaller part of an ocean, often partly enclosed by land.' },
    { question: 'What is a tide?', 'options': ['The rise and fall of the sea level', 'The movement of the ocean currents', 'The temperature of the ocean water', 'The color of the ocean water'], 'answer': 'The rise and fall of the sea level', explanation: 'Tides are when the ocean water slowly rises up the beach (high tide) and then goes back down (low tide) each day.' },
    { question: 'What causes the tides?', 'options': ["The Moon's gravity", "The Sun's gravity", "The Earth's rotation", "All of the above"], 'answer': "All of the above", explanation: 'It\'s a team effort! The Moon\'s gravity does most of the work pulling the water, but the Sun\'s gravity and Earth\'s spinning help too.' }
